19 son, while the person is residing in the correctional facility, for the purpose of establishing eligi-
20 bility for medical assistance prior to release, with full benefits upon the person’s release from the
21 correctional facility or during a period of hospitalization that will occur outside of the correctional
22 facility.
23 (b) The designee may obtain information necessary to determine eligibility for medical assist-
24 ance, including the person’s Social Security number or information that is not otherwise subject to
25 disclosure under ORS 411.320 or 413.175. The information obtained under this paragraph may be
26 used only for the purpose of assisting the person in applying for medical assistance and may not be
27 redisclosed without the person’s authorization.
28 [(c) If the person is determined eligible for medical assistance, the effective date of the person’s
29 medical assistance shall be the date the person is released from the correctional facility or the date the
30 person begins the period of hospitalization outside of the correctional facility.]
31 (5) This section does not extend eligibility to an otherwise ineligible person or extend medical
32 assistance to a person if matching federal funds are not available to pay for the medical assistance.
