14 SECTION 40. ORS 475A.325 is amended to read:
15 475A.325. [Facilitator license; fees; rules.] (1) The facilitation of psilocybin services is subject to
16 regulation by the Oregon Health Authority.
17 (2) A psilocybin service facilitator must have a facilitator license issued by the authority. To
18 hold a facilitator license issued under this section, a psilocybin service facilitator shall:
19 (a) [Must] Apply for a license in the manner described in ORS 475A.245;
20 (b) [Must] Provide proof that the applicant is 21 years of age or older;
21 [(c) Must, until January 1, 2025, provide proof that the applicant has been a resident of this state
22 for two or more years;]
23 [(d)] (c) [Must] Have a high school diploma or equivalent education;
24 [(e)] (d) [Must] Submit evidence of completion of education and training prescribed and approved
25 by the authority;
26 [(f)] (e) [Must] Have passed an examination approved, administered or recognized by the au-
27 thority; and
28 [(g)] (f) [Must] Meet the requirements of any rule adopted by the authority under subsection (4)
29 of this section.
30 (3) The authority may not require a psilocybin service facilitator to have a degree from a uni-
31 versity, college, post-secondary institution[,] or other institution of higher education.
32 (4) The authority shall adopt rules that:
33 (a) Require a psilocybin service facilitator to annually renew a license issued under this section;
34 (b) Establish application, licensure and renewal of licensure fees for psilocybin service
35 facilitators; [and]
36 (c) Require a psilocybin service facilitator to meet any public health and safety standards and
37 industry best practices established by the authority by rule[.]; and
38 (d) Allow an applicant who has completed a psilocybin service facilitator training program
39 in another state if the training program is approved by the regulatory body responsible for
40 regulating psilocybin in that state and is approved by the authority. The authority may ap-
41 prove a training program described in this paragraph if the authority finds that the training
42 program is substantially similar to those training programs in this state that are approved
43 by the authority under ORS 475A.380.
44 (5) Fees adopted under subsection (4)(b) of this section:
45 (a) May not exceed, together with other fees collected under ORS 475A.210 to 475A.722, the cost
[31]

HB 4040
1 of administering ORS 475A.210 to 475A.722; and
2 (b) Shall be deposited in the Psilocybin Control and Regulation Fund established under ORS
3 475A.492.
