16 SECTION 47a. ORS 685.102 is amended to read:
17 685.102. (1) Except as provided in subsections (2) and (5) of this section, each person holding a
18 license under this chapter shall submit annually by December 31, evidence satisfactory to the
19 Oregon Board of Naturopathic Medicine of successful completion of an approved program of con-
20 tinuing education of at least 25 hours in naturopathic medicine, completed in the calendar year
21 preceding the date on which the evidence is submitted, and completion during the renewal period,
22 or documentation of completion within the previous 36 months, of:
23 (a) A pain management education program approved by the board and developed based on rec-
24 ommendations of the Pain Management Commission; or
25 (b) An equivalent pain management education program, as determined by the board.
26 (2) The board may exempt any person holding a license under this chapter from the require-
27 ments of subsection (1) of this section upon application showing evidence satisfactory to the board
28 of inability to comply with the requirements because of physical or mental condition or because of
29 other unusual or extenuating circumstances. However, a person may not be exempted from the re-
30 quirements of subsection (1) of this section more than once in any five-year period.
31 (3) Notwithstanding subsection (2) of this section, a person holding a license under this chapter
32 may be exempted from the requirements of subsection (1) of this section upon application showing
33 evidence satisfactory to the board that the applicant is or will be in the next calendar year at least
34 [70] 60 years of age and is retired or will retire in the next calendar year from the practice of
35 naturopathic medicine.
36 (4) The board shall require licensees to obtain continuing education for the use of
37 pharmacological substances for diagnostic, preventive and therapeutic purposes in order to maintain
38 current licensure.
39 (5) A person whose license is in inactive status must submit by December 31 of each year evi-
40 dence satisfactory to the board of completion of 10 hours of approved continuing education in the
41 calendar year preceding the date on which the evidence is submitted.
42 (6) Notwithstanding subsections (1), (2) and (5) of this section, in the case of an applicant under
43 ORS 685.100 (6)(b) for reactivation of an inactive license, the continuing education requirement for
44 reactivation shall be set by rule of the board.
