1 (f) The insurer or self-insured employer shall pay the costs of the medical examination and re-
2 lated services which are reasonably necessary to allow the worker to submit to any examination
3 requested under this section. As used in this paragraph, “related services” includes, but is not lim-
4 ited to, child care, travel, meals, lodging and an amount equivalent to the worker’s net lost wages
5 for the period during which the worker is absent if the worker does not receive benefits pursuant
6 to ORS 656.210 (4) during the period of absence. A claim for “related services” described in this
7 paragraph shall be made in the manner prescribed by the director.
8 (g) A worker who objects to the location of an independent medical examination must request
